{"name":"Basic Combat","permission":{"default":0,"fX6hawKB2NFYN6Nn":3},"flags":{},"content":"<table style=\"width: 62.6466%; height: 66px;\" border=\"1\">\n<tbody>\n<tr style=\"height: 16px;\">\n<td style=\"text-align: center; width: 64.5697%; height: 16px;\"><strong>On your turn, you may take...</strong></td>\n<td style=\"text-align: center; width: 34.7201%; height: 16px;\"><strong>&nbsp;Or...</strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 50px;\">\n<td style=\"text-align: center; width: 64.5697%; height: 50px;\">\n<div>1 Major Action; 1 Move Action; Any number of minor actions</div>\n</td>\n<td style=\"text-align: center; width: 34.7201%; height: 50px;\">1 Focus Action</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<h3><strong>Major Actions</strong></h3>\n<div>\n<table style=\"width: 99.439%;\" border=\"1\">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"text-align: center; width: 24.2898%;\">Damaging Attack</td>\n<td style=\"text-align: center; width: 17.0455%;\">Bane Attack</td>\n<td style=\"text-align: center; width: 17.1875%;\">Invoke Boon</td>\n<td style=\"text-align: center; width: 14.6307%;\">Assist Ally</td>\n<td style=\"text-align: center; width: 25.7102%;\">Extra Move Action</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n</div>\n<h3><strong>Move Actions</strong></h3>\n<div>\n<table style=\"width: 93.3306%; height: 16px;\" border=\"1\">\n<tbody>\n<tr style=\"height: 16px;\">\n<td style=\"text-align: center; width: 31.8182%; height: 16px;\">Move your Speed</td>\n<td style=\"width: 43.4659%; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">Take Special Movement</td>\n<td style=\"width: 23.8636%; text-align: center; height: 16px;\">Resist Banes</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n</div>\n<h3><strong>Minor Actions</strong></h3>\n<div>\n<table style=\"width: 95.6035%; height: 42px;\" border=\"1\">\n<tbody>\n<tr style=\"height: 16px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 17.8026%; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">Opportunity Attack</td>\n<td style=\"width: 31.9132%; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">Retrieve an item stored on your person</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 10px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 17.8026%; height: 10px; text-align: center;\">Sustain a Boon</td>\n<td style=\"width: 31.9132%; height: 10px; text-align: center;\">Make a learning roll to recall useful information</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 16px;\">\n<td style=\"width: 17.8026%; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">Draw/Sheathe Weapon</td>\n<td style=\"width: 31.9132%; height: 16px; text-align: center;\">Open a door/chest/drawer etc.</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n</div>\n<div><strong>&amp; </strong>Make a perception roll to observe your surroundings</div>\n<h3><strong>Focus Actions</strong></h3>\n<div>\n<table border=\"1\">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>Superior Action:</strong> Gain Adv1</td>\n<td style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>Charge:</strong> 2x speed + melee at dis</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n</div>\n<h3><strong>Interrupt Actions</strong></h3>\n<div>\n<table border=\"1\">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>Defend:&nbsp;</strong>Replace def with roll</td>\n<td style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>Improvise:&nbsp;</strong>React to combat situation</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n</div>\n<div><strong>Defend:&nbsp;</strong>After an enemy has rolled a successful attack against you or an ally, describe how you are defending then make an action roll using an appropriate attribute (protection, agility, might are typical). Can only defend 1 target</div>\n<div>If attr roll is higher than targeted defense score, the roll replaces the defense for that attack only.</div>\n<div><strong>Note:&nbsp;</strong>weapons with defensive property gain adv equal to the defensive value</div>\n<p><strong>Improvise:&nbsp;</strong>You may use your interrupt action in order to improvise a response to a combat situation (e.g., invoke flight boon on ally who fell off a cliff -- or dive to try to catch them before they fall).&nbsp; Should generally be limited to non-offensive reactions to assist allies. GM Fiat.</p>","_id":"0g4c6voI4r103CVk"}
{"name":"Legend Points","permission":{"default":0,"fX6hawKB2NFYN6Nn":3},"flags":{},"content":"<p>Characters start with 0, and have a max of 10 Legend Points</p>\n<p>Legend points should be rewarded when they use a flaw to a noteworthy disadvantage, or for strong roleplaying</p>\n<hr />\n<p>A PC may spend a maximum number of LPs equal to their <strong>level + 1</strong> to enhance a single roll</p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Before making an action roll</strong>, the PC declares how many legend points to spend</li>\n<li>PC gains <strong>Adv 1</strong> <strong>on the roll</strong> for each legend point spent</li>\n<li>PC gains <strong>+1 to the result</strong> of the roll for each legend point spent</li>\n</ul>","_id":"DwcBQjTcR2xypsNQ"}
{"name":"Make a Damaging Attack","permission":{"default":0,"fX6hawKB2NFYN6Nn":3},"flags":{},"content":"<ol>\n<li><strong>Determine Attribute vs Defense:&nbsp;</strong>All attacks are attribute vs defense</li>\n<li><strong>Choose your target:&nbsp;</strong>Range depends on melee, ranged, or supernatural</li>\n<li><strong>Roll your attack: </strong>Damage is equal to the amount you exceeded target defense. If you meet or exceed the defense, you deal a minimum of 3 damage</li>\n</ol>\n<div><strong>Guard:&nbsp;</strong>Protects against <strong>attacks that can be dodged, deflected, or avoided</strong> by cover</div>\n<div><strong>Toughness:&nbsp;</strong>Is used to against attacks that require <strong>bodily endurance, health, sturdines</strong></div>\n<div><strong>Resolve:&nbsp;</strong>Guards against <strong>mental assaults and deceptions</strong></div>\n<p>If an enemy is within melee reach of you, all ranged attacks have Dis1. Area attacks that do not include an adjacent square to the attacker are considered ranged attacks.</p>\n<div><strong>Exceptional Success</strong></div>\n<div>If you deal <strong>10 or more damage</strong>, you may <strong>apply one bane of PL &lt;= the attribute</strong> used for the atttack. The attack must also equal or exceed the appropriate defense of that Bane. This applies to all targets in a multi-target attack.</div>\n<p><strong>Alternatively</strong>, you may choose to <strong>disrupt the target's concentration</strong>. You cancel a single boon being sustained by the target of yoru attack. This also works with multi-target.</p>","_id":"IEaWDaFhusRRdS7s"}
{"name":"Multi-Targeting","permission":{"default":0,"fX6hawKB2NFYN6Nn":3},"flags":{},"content":"<div><strong>Melee: </strong>Any number of foes within reach. You suffer Dis = #targets</div>\n<div><strong>Ranged: </strong>Up to 5 foes all within a 25' squre within your range. Dis = #targets</div>\n<div><strong>Area Multi-Targeting</strong></div>\n<div>Area attacks are only possible with extraordinary attributes, special weapon property, or other rule that grants this without an extraordinary attribute. All friends and foes that fall in the area are subject to the attack</div>\n<div><strong>Cube:&nbsp;</strong>LxWxH designated by attacker.<strong> Dis = 1 per 5' length</strong> of cube sides</div>\n<div><strong>Line:&nbsp;</strong>5'wide x 10' long x 10' high. You may create several lines as part of a single attack as long as one corner of each line touches. <strong>Dis = #lines</strong></div>\n<div><strong>Cone:</strong> You target a cone that extends from your space to a length you designate. At any given point, the cone is as wide as its distance from you. <strong>Dis = 1 per 5' length</strong> of cone</div>","_id":"a3AOT3g1TUmw3CEW"}
{"name":"Banes & Boons","permission":{"default":0,"fX6hawKB2NFYN6Nn":3},"flags":{},"content":"<p><strong>Bane Attacks:&nbsp;</strong>Follow the <strong>same steps as a damaging attack</strong> using the appropriate attriubute for the Bane. If you exceed the targeted defense, the target suffers the bane at the highest PL you qualify for.&nbsp;<strong>Note</strong>: If using a weapon with the Bane trait, you may treat the PL as 1 level lower for meeting requirements and gain Adv on the attack.</p>\n<div><strong>Invoke Boon:</strong></div>\n<ol>\n<li><strong>Choose your target</strong>: Same steps as a damaging attack (including multi-target)</li>\n<li><strong>Roll to invoke</strong>: Roll using the appropriate attribute as determined by the boon</li>\n<li><strong>Determine PL</strong>: Each boon has a defined set of PLs. To invoke a boon at a specified PL, you must have an attribute score &gt;= the PL and your roll must pass the challenge rating <strong>(10 + 2xPL)</strong>. PL is determined after you roll, not before.</li>\n</ol>","_id":"h1qYUyqtCFITf22G"}
{"name":"Attack Range","permission":{"default":0,"fX6hawKB2NFYN6Nn":3},"flags":{},"content":"<div><strong>Physical Weapons</strong></div>\n<div>\n<table style=\"width: 72.5904%; height: 32px;\" border=\"1\">\n<tbody>\n<tr style=\"height: 16px;\">\n<td style=\"text-align: center; width: 38.8856%; height: 16px;\"><strong>Close Range</strong> (1 handed)</td>\n<td style=\"text-align: center; width: 12.9469%; height: 16px;\">25'</td>\n<td style=\"text-align: center; width: 38.3516%; height: 16px;\"><strong>Medium Range&nbsp;</strong>(2 handed)</td>\n<td style=\"text-align: center; width: 8.82165%; height: 16px;\">75'</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 16px;\">\n<td style=\"text-align: center; width: 38.8856%; height: 16px;\"><strong>Short Range</strong> (1 handed)</td>\n<td style=\"text-align: center; width: 12.9469%; height: 16px;\">50'</td>\n<td style=\"text-align: center; width: 38.3516%; height: 16px;\"><strong>Long Range&nbsp;</strong>(2-handed)</td>\n<td style=\"text-align: center; width: 8.82165%; height: 16px;\">125'</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n</div>\n<div style=\"text-align: left;\"><strong>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;Extreme Range</strong>: 300' (min dist 50')</div>\n<div style=\"text-align: left;\"><strong>Non-Physical Attack Range</strong></div>\n<div style=\"text-align: left;\">\n<table style=\"width: 31.3943%;\" border=\"1\">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width: 49.858%; text-align: center;\"><strong>Attr Score</strong></td>\n<td style=\"width: 16.3352%; text-align: center;\">1-3</td>\n<td style=\"width: 16.3352%; text-align: center;\">4-6</td>\n<td style=\"width: 16.4773%; text-align: center;\">7-9</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width: 49.858%; text-align: center;\"><strong>Range</strong></td>\n<td style=\"width: 16.3352%; text-align: center;\">25'</td>\n<td style=\"width: 16.3352%; text-align: center;\">50'</td>\n<td style=\"width: 16.4773%; text-align: center;\">75'</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n</div>","_id":"lNAcTNKAFYfUzrSL"}
{"name":"Damage and Healing","permission":{"default":0,"fX6hawKB2NFYN6Nn":3},"flags":{},"content":"<div><strong>Finishing Blows</strong></div>\n<div>If attacked while unable to defend yourself, the attack may cause immediate death. Your defense does not include any bonuses from attributes. Any damage dealt requires a fort roll with<strong> CR=10+damage dealt. If you fail, you die.</strong></div>\n<p><strong>Reaching Zero Hit Points:&nbsp;</strong>You fall unconscious and are helpless. Healing to above 0 causes you to regain consciousness</p>\n<p><strong>Heailng After Combat:&nbsp;</strong>After at least <strong>10 minutes of rest</strong>, your HP is returned to maximum if you are conscious. If unconscious, you regain consciousness and all HP after 2d4 hours.</p>\n<p><strong>Lethal Damage</strong>: When suffering lethal damage, your max HP is reduced by the amount of lethal damage sustained. Lethal damage heals 1HP per day per fortitude. With full-time care, the rate includes the capable healer's attribute score (e.g., learning, presence, creation)</p>","_id":"xSvr0Z4Sk752HBkM"}
